Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Peel and halve @carrot{1}(peeled and halved lengthwise), then thinly slice into half-moons. Halve, peel, and dice @red onion{1}(peeled and diced). Chop @zucchini{1}(chopped into ½-inch pieces). Roughly chop @dried apricots{1.5%oz}(roughly chopped). Zest and halve @lemon{1}(zested and halved).

> TIP: Skip zesting if you prefer to save some time.

== Bulgur Paella ==

In a large #ovenproof pan{}, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} over medium-high heat. Add carrots and zucchini, and toss until just tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove from pan and set aside.

In same pan, heat another drizzle of olive oil over medium heat. Add onions and toss until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add @bulgur wheat{1/2%cup} and apricots, and stir to coat in oil. Add 1 1/4 cups water and @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and bring to a boil.

Stir carrots, zucchini, and lemon zest into pan. Season with salt and pepper. If you don't have an #ovenproof pan{}, transfer contents to a #baking dish{}. Bake uncovered until water is absorbed and bulgur is tender, about ~{10%minutes}.

> TIP: If liquid absorbs too quickly, add a splash of water as needed.

== Chicken ==

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in another large pan over medium-high heat. Season @chicken breasts{12%oz} on all sides with salt and pepper. Sear until browned and no longer pink in the middle, ~{5-7%minutes} per side.

== To Serve ==

Chop @parsley{1/4%oz}(chopped) and cut lemon into wedges. Place chicken on top of paella. Sprinkle with parsley, serve with lemon wedges, and enjoy!